    Enhance search functionality and improve documentation layout (#3647)

    This pull request introduces a new, modern search experience for the
    documentation site by adding an overlay search modal that can be
    triggered from the navigation bar or via keyboard shortcuts. The changes
    focus on improving usability and accessibility of the search
    functionality.

    **User interface enhancements:**

    * Added a search icon button to the navigation bar, allowing users to
    easily access the search overlay.
    * Introduced a visually prominent search overlay modal, which includes a
    styled search form and a close button for improved user experience.
    * Hid the legacy inline search form in favor of the overlay modal,
    reducing clutter in the main layout.

    **Accessibility and interaction improvements:**

    * Implemented JavaScript logic to handle opening the search overlay via
    click or keyboard shortcut (Ctrl/Cmd+K), focusing the input
    automatically, and closing the overlay via Escape key or clicking
    outside the modal.
    * Enabled form submission directly from the overlay search input using
    the Enter key for a smoother search workflow.

    ---------

    Co-authored-by: vfdev <vfdev.5@gmail.com>
