    Updating the docs to use default sphinx search (#3636)

    This pull request updates the documentation build and layout, primarily
    removing Algolia DocSearch integration and related customizations, and
    updating Sphinx requirements. The main changes are grouped below:

    **Search Functionality Updates:**

    * Removed Algolia DocSearch integration from the documentation by
    deleting the search widget, its initialization script, and all related
    CSS customizations in `layout.html` and `ignite_theme.css`. Replaced it
    with a simpler, built-in search form.
    [[1]](diffhunk://#diff-04cc0b7b8020c120d4d8b9679aaa1d63ea9c7b0d7b483c5c0bc6272501100c03L199-R205)
    [[2]](diffhunk://#diff-04cc0b7b8020c120d4d8b9679aaa1d63ea9c7b0d7b483c5c0bc6272501100c03L519-L537)
    [[3]](diffhunk://#diff-c1b65b41192c2aca198b8eee61054f429546967896a07597db411d92c45c22c8L178-L217)
    * Removed the preconnect link to Algolia's CDN from the HTML layout.

    **Documentation Build System:**

    * Updated the Sphinx requirement in `requirements.txt` to version 7
    (from <6), ensuring compatibility with newer Sphinx features and themes.

    **HTML/CSS Improvements:**

    * Made the inclusion of custom stylesheet conditional on the presence of
    the `style` variable in the HTML template, improving template
    robustness.
